The specified chunk consists of event handler methods (`_handleTyping` and `_handleErasing`) within a class managing user input processing for a GUI element. These methods are triggered when the user types or deletes characters, respectively, and they ensure proper text capitalization by invoking the `_autoCapitalize` method. This functionality is part of an entry widget or similar UI component that handles real-time text adjustments to maintain consistent formatting as users interact with it.

def _handleTyping(self, guiEvent):
        self._autoCapitalize()

    def _handleErasing(self, guiEvent):
        self._autoCapitalize()
